1
00:00:01,000 --> 00:00:04,000
{\an8}<b><font color="#9CD5FF">One Pace Premium</font></b>
Keep the project alive: <font color="#a8c7fa">ko-fi.com/not6ip</font>

2
00:01:34,940 --> 00:01:39,900
Linlin! I'll put you out of your misery
with my own hands!

3
00:01:42,650 --> 00:01:44,610
Semlor...

4
00:02:03,710 --> 00:02:05,010
No, Linlin!

5
00:02:06,480 --> 00:02:07,890
Se...

6
00:02:07,890 --> 00:02:09,100
Jorl!

7
00:02:09,100 --> 00:02:11,110
m...

8
00:02:11,110 --> 00:02:12,520
lor !

9
00:02:34,030 --> 00:02:35,670
Chief Waterfall Beard!

10
00:02:35,670 --> 00:02:37,110
Chief Jorl!

11
00:02:40,760 --> 00:02:43,590
Semlor !

12
00:02:43,590 --> 00:02:45,020
Hold Linlin!

13
00:02:45,020 --> 00:02:47,170
Put out the fire in the village!

14
00:02:48,220 --> 00:02:51,050
– Catch her already!
– Okay!

15
00:02:51,050 --> 00:02:53,360
Don't hurt her!

16
00:02:53,360 --> 00:02:54,860
Can you make some semlor ?

17
00:02:54,860 --> 00:02:57,450
There's some for the festival
in the village storehouse!

18
00:02:57,450 --> 00:02:58,870
Bring them now!

19
00:02:58,870 --> 00:03:00,650
O-Okay!

20
00:03:09,350 --> 00:03:12,620
– Mother, what are you doing?!
– It's dangerous!

21
00:03:12,620 --> 00:03:14,450
Stay back!

22
00:03:26,820 --> 00:03:28,950
Gebur...

23
00:03:37,560 --> 00:03:41,060
Mother!

24
00:03:50,640 --> 00:03:54,010
...tstag!
"Gerburtstag" - Birthday

25
00:03:59,920 --> 00:04:02,470
Mother!

26
00:04:02,520 --> 00:04:04,560
I shall give you a voice.

27
00:04:09,400 --> 00:04:11,070
What's that?

28
00:04:23,810 --> 00:04:26,280
Heed my command.

29
00:04:27,570 --> 00:04:29,600
– There's a face in the fire!
– What?!

30
00:04:29,600 --> 00:04:31,620
I'm scared...

31
00:04:32,000 --> 00:04:33,660
It's like a demon!

32
00:04:35,400 --> 00:04:38,610
Your name is Pandora!

33
00:04:41,670 --> 00:04:43,050
I brought it!

34
00:04:43,050 --> 00:04:45,040
Hurry up and feed her!

35
00:04:45,880 --> 00:04:47,280
Semlor !

36
00:04:47,280 --> 00:04:49,430
It's delicious! It's delicious!

37
00:04:51,630 --> 00:04:53,770
Simmer down!

38
00:05:24,240 --> 00:05:26,480
The fire...

39
00:05:26,480 --> 00:05:28,050
is gone.

40
00:05:28,720 --> 00:05:30,050
Hey, look!

41
00:05:32,470 --> 00:05:34,180
How cute!

42
00:05:34,180 --> 00:05:36,020
Hi, Mother!

43
00:05:36,020 --> 00:05:37,600
Mother...

44
00:05:37,600 --> 00:05:39,690
...worked a miracle!

45
00:05:39,690 --> 00:05:43,190
No, it wasn't me.

46
00:05:44,850 --> 00:05:48,890
The sun god calmed this disaster.

47
00:05:51,190 --> 00:05:54,440
I'm so happy!

48
00:05:55,660 --> 00:06:01,190
Punish her... She is not just a child...

49
00:06:01,190 --> 00:06:08,180
If we don't do something now...
she'll bring even more disaster in the future!

50
00:06:08,840 --> 00:06:11,220
– Chief Jorl!
– Quick, help him!

51
00:06:13,250 --> 00:06:15,220
Chief Mountain Beard!

52
00:06:16,840 --> 00:06:18,810
Linlin...

53
00:06:24,940 --> 00:06:26,760
Please forgive her!

54
00:06:32,190 --> 00:06:35,160
You're trying to stop me, Carmel?

55
00:06:36,610 --> 00:06:41,650
Jorl has been my companion in battle for 300 years.

56
00:06:44,910 --> 00:06:49,490
He's too old. I don't think he'll survive this time.

57
00:06:50,000 --> 00:06:55,930
Being a warrior isn't about living long...
It's about how you die!

58
00:06:56,420 --> 00:06:58,500
We have to bring it to an end...

59
00:06:58,500 --> 00:07:03,360
We cannot forgive those
who defy Elbaf’s laws.

60
00:07:03,360 --> 00:07:07,150
I understand!
But even if she can't be forgiven,

61
00:07:07,150 --> 00:07:11,320
Linlin is a poor child who was abandoned.

62
00:07:11,320 --> 00:07:15,200
She is now under the care
of the House of Lambs!

63
00:07:15,200 --> 00:07:18,310
I cannot abandon her!

64
00:07:19,650 --> 00:07:22,000
What will you do with her?

65
00:07:22,940 --> 00:07:27,960
I will take her and leave this place!

66
00:07:29,130 --> 00:07:30,090
Carmel!

67
00:07:34,970 --> 00:07:38,080
Chief Mountain Beard!
You must kill Linlin!

68
00:07:38,080 --> 00:07:43,150
Why should we pardon her
after she's done such a horrible thing?!

69
00:07:43,150 --> 00:07:45,900
What has happened to your Elbaf pride?

70
00:07:56,970 --> 00:08:01,780
Alright then, why don't you
get out of my sight now?!

71
00:08:05,490 --> 00:08:06,740
Why?!

72
00:08:06,740 --> 00:08:07,480
Hajrudin!

73
00:08:07,480 --> 00:08:12,000
Let go of me! Let go!

74
00:08:20,720 --> 00:08:23,220
What happened to Chief Waterfall Beard?

75
00:08:23,900 --> 00:08:25,760
He died.

76
00:08:25,760 --> 00:08:28,440
Doesn't she remember?

77
00:08:29,180 --> 00:08:33,530
Jorl, the hero of the giants, died,

78
00:08:34,950 --> 00:08:39,900
and between the devastation of Linlin and Carmel's miracle...

79
00:08:41,580 --> 00:08:44,120
the events of that day...

80
00:08:44,120 --> 00:08:50,880
spread far and wide through the few settlements of giants around the world.

81
00:08:50,880 --> 00:08:55,300
With the orphans of the House of Lambs,
who couldn't stand to be apart from their mother,

82
00:08:55,300 --> 00:09:00,390
along with the giants' new sworn enemy,
Charlotte Linlin, in tow,

83
00:09:00,390 --> 00:09:04,540
Mother Carmel left Elbaf.

84
00:09:04,540 --> 00:09:10,300
And then, they began life anew
at a reestablished House of Lambs.

85
00:09:10,300 --> 00:09:12,800
It's done! Is this good enough?

86
00:09:12,800 --> 00:09:17,360
That's all we need.
I'm sorry for asking these favors.

87
00:09:17,360 --> 00:09:23,750
Without your help, there's no way we'd have a house
this far into the mountains.

88
00:09:23,750 --> 00:09:28,210
Don't mention it. To be honest,
I don't wanna see Linlin's face,

89
00:09:28,210 --> 00:09:32,360
but you're the Holy Mother
to us giants too, Carmel.

90
00:09:32,360 --> 00:09:34,060
If you ever need us, say the word!

91
00:09:34,060 --> 00:09:35,740
Thank you!

92
00:09:36,580 --> 00:09:43,100
To put the worried children at ease,
Carmel began to smile even more.

93
00:09:45,060 --> 00:09:47,270
Wait, wait!

94
00:09:47,270 --> 00:09:53,250
A few days after leaving Elbaf,
things were just as they used to be...

95
00:09:53,250 --> 00:09:55,800
No, Linlin's gonna kill me!

96
00:09:55,800 --> 00:09:58,490
Wait, wait!

97
00:09:58,990 --> 00:10:03,950
And the House of Lambs was filled
with the children's laughter once more.

98
00:10:03,950 --> 00:10:05,970
Look after the house while I'm away.

99
00:10:05,970 --> 00:10:08,100
I'll clean the bathroom!

100
00:10:08,100 --> 00:10:10,330
I'll do the laundry!

101
00:10:10,330 --> 00:10:13,200
When will you be back?

102
00:10:13,200 --> 00:10:16,530
I'll be back once I finish buying our groceries.

103
00:10:16,530 --> 00:10:18,730
Do you need anything?

104
00:10:19,480 --> 00:10:20,890
Shortcake!

105
00:10:20,890 --> 00:10:23,680
– A set of cards!
– Toy swords for samurai fighting!

106
00:10:23,680 --> 00:10:25,710
Okay.

107
00:10:26,560 --> 00:10:30,460
See you, Mother! Take care!

108
00:10:33,360 --> 00:10:36,680
To the rest of the world,
the House of Lambs was a place...

109
00:10:37,520 --> 00:10:40,800
where the pious mother would
miraculously reform troubled children

110
00:10:40,800 --> 00:10:43,830
until they were ready for a good home...

111
00:10:49,520 --> 00:10:51,510
You're right on time...

112
00:10:52,970 --> 00:10:59,010
Of course. Have I ever stood you up?

113
00:10:59,010 --> 00:11:01,890
Let's get to business.

114
00:11:07,690 --> 00:11:10,900
There is a good girl.

115
00:11:16,660 --> 00:11:19,440
I never thought you'd leave Elbaf...

116
00:11:20,120 --> 00:11:24,000
I had to. I didn't want to give this girl up.

117
00:11:37,800 --> 00:11:39,900
Think about it.

118
00:11:39,900 --> 00:11:44,600
At just five years old, she was able
to destroy half of an Elbaf village.

119
00:11:44,600 --> 00:11:46,660
But the price you're asking for is...

120
00:11:46,660 --> 00:11:48,980
I know you can pay it.

121
00:11:48,980 --> 00:11:52,830
If she were in the Navy, she could one day
be an admiral or even the fleet admiral.

122
00:11:52,830 --> 00:11:57,410
If she were in Cipher Pol, she'd be
a great shield for the Celestial Dragons.

123
00:11:58,820 --> 00:12:02,000
I've been in the kid-trafficking business for 50 years,

124
00:12:02,000 --> 00:12:05,580
and this girl's the finest product I've ever had!

125
00:12:06,790 --> 00:12:12,210
After pulling that stunt with the Navy 37 years ago,
I was able to live on Elbaf...

126
00:12:12,210 --> 00:12:18,020
which got you guys the first-ever
giant recruit for the Navy... John Giant!

127
00:12:18,020 --> 00:12:20,970
That was all thanks to me!

128
00:12:21,910 --> 00:12:25,600
I run the House of Lambs nice and clean,
and those kids have no idea

129
00:12:25,600 --> 00:12:30,150
that I've been selling the liveliest of them
to the government every two years.

130
00:12:30,840 --> 00:12:34,070
Orphans make good spies, right?

131
00:12:34,070 --> 00:12:36,300
They've got no history to trace!

132
00:12:36,300 --> 00:12:39,370
All right! All right!
I'll get you your money!

133
00:12:40,120 --> 00:12:42,490
Of course you will!

134
00:12:42,490 --> 00:12:45,850
It ain't easy being the Holy Mother.

135
00:12:45,870 --> 00:12:52,590
Mother Carmel
Orphan Seller
(Code Name: "Mountain Witch")

136
00:12:46,630 --> 00:12:52,340
I think I'll take the chance to retire after this one,

137
00:12:52,340 --> 00:12:57,050
so this'll be my last deal. I need you to pay me in full.

138
00:13:01,580 --> 00:13:04,350
What do you all wanna sing today?

139
00:13:04,350 --> 00:13:06,600
"Binks' Sake"!

140
00:13:06,600 --> 00:13:09,560
Really? But that's a pirates' song.

141
00:13:09,560 --> 00:13:12,650
That's right!
We're gonna be pirates someday!

142
00:13:12,650 --> 00:13:15,070
Oh, that sounds cool!

143
00:13:17,700 --> 00:13:21,870
♪ Making a delivery,
bringing it across the sea ♪

144
00:13:21,870 --> 00:13:25,950
♪ Binks' sake in the hold
as we sail through the breeze ♪

145
00:13:25,950 --> 00:13:30,250
♪ Far across the eye can see,
the sun is shining merrily ♪

146
00:13:30,250 --> 00:13:34,840
♪ As the birds fly in the sky
as they sing out with glee ♪

147
00:13:32,750 --> 00:13:37,090
You'll be sold to the government
before you get the chance to become pirates.

148
00:13:34,840 --> 00:13:39,250
♪ Bid adieu to everyone,
so long to port renowned ♪

149
00:13:39,250 --> 00:13:43,660
♪ Sailing on from dusk 'til dawn
and singing out as one ♪

150
00:13:43,660 --> 00:13:47,940
♪ Cross the gold and silver waves,
changing into water sprays ♪

151
00:13:47,940 --> 00:13:52,550
♪ Sailing out on our journey
to the ends of the sea! ♪

152
00:13:52,550 --> 00:13:55,250
One, two, three!

153
00:13:55,250 --> 00:14:00,210
Happy birthday, Linlin!

154
00:13:55,250 --> 00:13:57,200
"Happy birthday, Linlin".

155
00:14:02,660 --> 00:14:06,510
Thank you, everyone!

156
00:14:06,510 --> 00:14:12,020
We know how much you love semlor, Linlin.... So we made a croquembouche out of them!

157
00:14:12,020 --> 00:14:13,980
I hope it's good!

158
00:14:13,980 --> 00:14:17,900
It's called croquembouche ?
It looks delicious!

159
00:14:20,820 --> 00:14:22,190
Let's have a tea party!

160
00:14:22,190 --> 00:14:23,700
A tea party?

161
00:14:23,700 --> 00:14:29,820
We'll spend time gracefully sitting around tables,
drinking tea, and eating sweets!

162
00:14:29,820 --> 00:14:33,420
That sounds great!
I wanna have that! A tea party!

163
00:14:33,420 --> 00:14:35,800
– Let's make tea.
– Join us, Mother!

164
00:14:35,800 --> 00:14:37,540
Okay, okay.

165
00:14:37,900 --> 00:14:39,380
Thank you!

166
00:14:39,380 --> 00:14:40,500
Yay!

167
00:14:42,230 --> 00:14:44,150
Alright, let's start!

168
00:14:44,150 --> 00:14:46,760
– Eat as much as you want!
– Eat, eat!

169
00:14:46,760 --> 00:14:49,280
Uh-huh! Thank you!

170
00:14:50,800 --> 00:14:53,840
It's so delicious!

171
00:14:55,350 --> 00:14:57,350
She eats so fast!

172
00:15:00,320 --> 00:15:03,150
The tea party's fun!

173
00:15:04,420 --> 00:15:08,530
I'm so happy! It's so delicious!

174
00:15:09,160 --> 00:15:13,290
One day, Mother Carmel simply vanished.

175
00:15:13,290 --> 00:15:19,380
And it happened on the very best birthday
that Linlin had ever had.

176
00:15:25,080 --> 00:15:29,090
She was with her friends at the House of Lambs,
kids who'd been through the same hardships,

177
00:15:29,620 --> 00:15:32,890
and her beloved, kindhearted mother.

178
00:15:33,310 --> 00:15:39,060
Surrounded by all those smiles,
and eating her delicious, sweet birthday cake,

179
00:15:39,060 --> 00:15:43,230
Linlin was unable to hold back her tears.

180
00:15:43,230 --> 00:15:45,360
Eat as much as you like, Linlin.

181
00:15:45,360 --> 00:15:47,860
I'll eat... I'll eat it all!

182
00:15:48,460 --> 00:15:54,070
What a wonderful day it was...
She couldn't even see through her tears.

183
00:15:56,700 --> 00:15:59,400
Hey, hey, don't rush, Linlin!

184
00:15:59,400 --> 00:16:01,500
We made it for you!

185
00:16:01,500 --> 00:16:02,960
It's all for you, Linlin!

186
00:16:02,960 --> 00:16:04,980
Thank you!

187
00:16:08,630 --> 00:16:10,050
Eat more!

188
00:16:10,050 --> 00:16:12,180
Let's stay friends!

189
00:16:12,180 --> 00:16:13,500
Uh-huh, uh-huh!

190
00:16:15,360 --> 00:16:17,890
Let's stay together and have fun!

191
00:16:17,890 --> 00:16:19,020
Yeah!

192
00:16:19,020 --> 00:16:21,590
It's so delicious!

193
00:16:21,590 --> 00:16:25,910
What a truly wonderful birthday.

194
00:16:25,910 --> 00:16:27,700
Lick!

195
00:16:27,700 --> 00:16:33,900
Oh, I'm so happy! I was eating so much,
that I even chewed off a bit of the table.

196
00:16:33,900 --> 00:16:39,780
Thank you, everyone!
I'll never forget this day for the rest of my...

197
00:16:45,700 --> 00:16:47,230
What?

198
00:16:47,500 --> 00:16:50,020
Everyone?

199
00:16:50,020 --> 00:16:51,230
Mother?

200
00:16:52,200 --> 00:16:56,190
One day, Mother Carmel...

201
00:16:54,650 --> 00:16:56,200
Where did they go?

202
00:16:56,200 --> 00:16:58,980
...suddenly vanished.

203
00:16:58,980 --> 00:17:02,150
Hmm? Huh?

204
00:17:02,150 --> 00:17:05,780
Where are you?! Everyone!
Are you in the house?

205
00:17:17,840 --> 00:17:19,650
Hey!

206
00:17:21,360 --> 00:17:23,220
Everyone!

207
00:17:25,760 --> 00:17:26,930
Linlin!

208
00:17:31,810 --> 00:17:34,230
Oh, there you are!

209
00:17:34,680 --> 00:17:36,290
What?

210
00:17:43,440 --> 00:17:46,620
Don't leave me all alone...

211
00:17:49,570 --> 00:17:52,580
Where are you, everyone?

212
00:18:01,820 --> 00:18:04,840
Hey, Mother...

213
00:18:04,840 --> 00:18:09,220
Why did you just vanish?

214
00:18:21,600 --> 00:18:24,000
Where did you go,

215
00:18:24,000 --> 00:18:27,060
Mother?!

216
00:18:27,060 --> 00:18:28,910
Mama!

217
00:18:29,660 --> 00:18:35,050
63 years ago, Mother Carmel
and the other children simply vanished.

218
00:18:35,940 --> 00:18:38,600
Even Big Mom herself does not know
the truth of what happened,

219
00:18:38,600 --> 00:18:43,550
but there were two people
who witnessed the whole thing...

220
00:18:44,850 --> 00:18:46,980
Where did you go?

221
00:18:46,980 --> 00:18:51,500
One was a warrior of Elbaf who was worried about the House of Lambs,

222
00:18:51,500 --> 00:18:53,270
so he came to check on them.

223
00:18:53,970 --> 00:18:56,200
M-Monster!

224
00:18:56,200 --> 00:18:59,160
The giant went pale, took off running,

225
00:18:59,160 --> 00:19:02,940
and never returned to the island.

226
00:19:05,020 --> 00:19:10,450
Eventually, news of this day spread to Elbaf,
and then to all the giants in the world,

227
00:19:10,450 --> 00:19:15,620
and from that point onward,
the name "Charlotte Linlin" became

228
00:19:15,620 --> 00:19:19,120
so hated that
no giant would utter her name.

229
00:19:22,220 --> 00:19:26,750
Where did you go?! Mother! Everyone!

230
00:19:26,750 --> 00:19:30,220
Meanwhile, the other witness

231
00:19:30,220 --> 00:19:35,140
was a failed pirate cook
who'd wound up living on the island

232
00:19:35,140 --> 00:19:37,640
named Streusen.

233
00:19:42,780 --> 00:19:46,010
He found it to be very entertaining.

234
00:20:01,940 --> 00:20:03,740
He had the ability

235
00:20:03,740 --> 00:20:06,900
to turn any object into food,

236
00:20:06,900 --> 00:20:09,260
thanks to his Cook-Cook Fruit.

237
00:20:16,280 --> 00:20:18,890
I've never seen a monster like that before.

238
00:20:18,890 --> 00:20:22,100
Don't leave me alone...

239
00:20:23,540 --> 00:20:26,980
At this rate, she's gonna die.
What a waste that'd be.

240
00:20:33,330 --> 00:20:35,780
Where did you go, Mother?

241
00:20:38,220 --> 00:20:41,460
Hey, what's the matter, little girl?

242
00:20:41,460 --> 00:20:44,460
If you keep crying,
you're just going to get hungrier.

243
00:20:45,320 --> 00:20:50,200
Say, little girl,
shall we talk about your dreams?

244
00:20:50,200 --> 00:20:51,800
Who are you, old man?

245
00:20:51,800 --> 00:20:53,550
Hey, don't come too close.

246
00:20:53,550 --> 00:20:59,640
Hey, old man, have you seen Mother?
Do you know where everyone's gone?

247
00:20:59,640 --> 00:21:03,030
I don't know,
but I bet they'll come back soon.

248
00:21:03,500 --> 00:21:04,800
You think so?

249
00:21:04,800 --> 00:21:07,640
Yeah, I'll stay with you until then.

250
00:21:07,640 --> 00:21:12,740
I'm a good chef.
You won't go hungry with me around.

251
00:21:16,200 --> 00:21:19,280
I'm hungry...

252
00:21:19,280 --> 00:21:21,690
You can count on me.

253
00:21:40,980 --> 00:21:42,480
See?

254
00:21:42,480 --> 00:21:49,070
It was the meeting of these two
that led to the formation of the Big Mom Pirates.

255
00:22:07,040 --> 00:22:09,210
Linlin!

256
00:22:09,210 --> 00:22:12,710
Come to your senses!
They're going to shoot you!

257
00:22:13,640 --> 00:22:16,300
So, at the tea party today,

258
00:22:16,300 --> 00:22:21,170
if we break that picture in half,
what do you think will happen?

259
00:22:21,770 --> 00:22:23,600
Mama will be devastated!

260
00:22:23,600 --> 00:22:28,610
And no one there will be able to move
for more than five seconds.

261
00:22:28,610 --> 00:22:32,820
Then, the KX launcher
will show its real strength...

262
00:22:34,110 --> 00:22:37,490
and Emperor Big Mom will die!

263
00:22:43,640 --> 00:22:46,290
You're doomed, Big Mom!

264
00:22:47,640 --> 00:22:49,040
Mama!

265
00:23:07,640 --> 00:23:09,920
Mother.

266
00:23:09,920 --> 00:23:13,280
They're all trying to stop me.

267
00:23:17,840 --> 00:23:23,910
People are happiest when they're equal.

268
00:23:23,910 --> 00:23:29,590
But in today's world, a country like that
is nearly impossible to find.

269
00:23:29,590 --> 00:23:34,130
That's why we should start our own country here!

270
00:23:34,130 --> 00:23:37,800
It'll be a country where everyone is equal!

271
00:23:37,800 --> 00:23:39,180
Country?!

272
00:23:39,180 --> 00:23:43,200
That's right. A place where
all races can coexist in peace.

273
00:23:43,200 --> 00:23:46,100
And where everyone
will be at the same eye level!

274
00:23:46,850 --> 00:23:49,690
The same eye level? That sounds great!

275
00:23:50,120 --> 00:23:53,270
Then everyone can be big like me!

276
00:23:54,070 --> 00:23:56,440
Wow! How cool!

277
00:23:56,990 --> 00:23:59,650
That's a beautiful dream, Mother!

278
00:24:05,540 --> 00:24:08,580
Linlin!

279
00:24:09,640 --> 00:24:13,670
Everyone, let's work hard together.

280
00:24:13,870 --> 00:24:15,200
I'll do my best!

281
00:24:15,200 --> 00:24:16,780
– Me too!
– Me too!

282
00:24:16,780 --> 00:24:18,400
Yeah!

283
00:24:18,400 --> 00:24:21,330
Let's create a country of dreams right here!

284
00:24:21,330 --> 00:24:23,640
I'll do my best too, Mother!

285
00:24:23,640 --> 00:24:26,720
You're a good girl, Linlin.

286
00:24:27,280 --> 00:24:28,600
I am!

287
00:24:28,600 --> 00:24:33,950
If there were countries like that,
the world would be a much more peaceful place.

288
00:24:33,950 --> 00:24:38,610
Everyone would be able to find happiness.

289
00:24:41,240 --> 00:24:45,450
Mother's dream was my dream!

290
00:24:45,900 --> 00:24:50,080
Peace? Is that your dream, Linlin?

291
00:24:50,080 --> 00:24:56,750
It is! I'm gonna build a country
that Mother would like!

292
00:25:10,320 --> 00:25:13,140
Why don't you stop crying already?

293
00:25:13,140 --> 00:25:17,730
Hey, hey, hey! I wanna see Mother's magic!

294
00:25:17,730 --> 00:25:18,740
Magic?

295
00:25:18,740 --> 00:25:22,950
Yeah, she was good at doing magic tricks.

296
00:25:22,950 --> 00:25:26,120
I think she put out her hands like this...

297
00:25:28,620 --> 00:25:30,870
Then...

298
